'''''Young Jedi Knights: Jedi Bounty''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] young-adult novel written by [[Kevin J. Anderson]] and [[Rebecca Moesta]]. It is the tenth book in the ''[[Star Wars: Young Jedi Knights]]'' series, and it was first published by [[Berkley Boulevard]] in [[October]] [[1997]].

The novel was reprinted in ''[[Young Jedi Knights: The Fall of the Diversity Alliance]]'' ([[1998]]).

==Publisher's summary==
''Lowbacca has left the Jedi academy and traveled to the planet Ryloth, headquarters of the Diversity Alliance, to see what the Diversity Alliance is really all about.''

''On Yavin 4, Jacen, Jaina and the other young Jedi Knights have already discovered one truth about the Alliance&mdash;once you go to Ryloth, you either join or you die. Lowie is in great danger, and they must rescue him. But what can a small group of humans do against a planet full of hostile aliens?''

==Plot summary==
Having been convinced by his friend [[Raabakyysh|Raaba]] that [[Human/Legends|Humans]] had never atoned for their atrocities committed under the [[New Order/Legends|New Order]], the [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] [[Lowbacca]] goes to [[Ryloth/Legends|Ryloth]] to join the [[Anti-Humanism|anti-Human]] [[Diversity Alliance]]. Meanwhile, at the [[Jedi Praxeum|Jedi Academy]], his fellow [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] trainees [[Darth Caedus|Jacen]], [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina]], [[Tenel Ka Djo|Tenel Ka]], and [[Raynar Thul]] voyage to [[Ryloth/Legends|Ryloth]] to learn what they can about the [[Diversity Alliance]], hoping to stop the organization.

There, they see that [[Nolaa Tarkona]] is stockpiling supplies, gearing up for full war against the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] and on the [[Human/Legends|Human]] species in retaliation for the crimes of the [[Humanocentrism|Humanocentric]] [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. However, the young Jedi are discovered and [[Prison/Legends|captured]], and Tarkona sentences them to toil in the [[Ryll/Legends|ryll]] [[Mining/Legends|mines]].

[[Zekk]] finds [[Bornan Thul]], saving him from pursuit by [[Dengar/Legends|Dengar]] the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]]. Bornan reveals to Zekk details about the [[Emperor's Plague]] and provides him coordinates to the [[Emperor's plague storehouse|storehouse]] where supplies of the pathogen can be found. Bornan hopes Zekk can stop Tarkona before is too late. Zekk passes word of Tarkona's plan to [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke]] on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]], and Luke leads a mission to Ryloth to rescue the captive Jedi with the help of Lowbacca and [[Sirrakuk|Sirra]].

